<TITLE> All BNP names wiped for 2 Ctg seats </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)  Nomination of all BNP candidates for two seats in Chittagong were cancelled on scrutiny on Thursday. The candidacy of BNP's Giasuddin Kader Chowdhury for Chittaging -5 was cancelled as he defaulted on payment of bank loan. The nominations of former BNP lawmaker Mostafa Kamal Pasha and independent candidate Mostafa Kamal Pasha Babul, who recently joined the BNP, for Chittagong-16 seat (Sandwip) were also cancelled. For this seat, BNP leader Nurul Mostafa submitted nomination paper as an independent candidate but his nomination was also cancelled since he was a defaulter. Returning officer district commissioner Ashraf Shamim canceled former MP Pasha's nomination as his statement and his income tax returns did not match. The nomination of Zahir Hossain, another candidate for this seat, was cancelled due to errors. bd
